The paper discusses the state-of-the-art computational models for language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the analysis and synthesis of long distance dependencies in sequential datasets, which can be relevant to other areas of artificial intelligence such as computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of synthetic datasets, which can be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
